        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Beckenham Kent</placeName>
                    <salute>My dear Huxley</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have asked Hooker to forward the memorial, &amp; after signing it, please place it in the enclosed envelope. for me.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>N.B. Letters placed in pillar post even so late at night reach Down at noon next day.— I read a few days ago in the Times a splendid Lecture by you before the Zoolog. Soc on Evolution.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>How I do hope that all our trouble about the memorial may be successful.—</p>
<p>Ever Yours | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.2 the] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">2.2 in the Times] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
            </div>
            
             
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The date is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12953.xml">letter to P. L. Sclater, 29 December 1880</ref>. </note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2357.xml">Joseph Dalton Hooker</ref> was the most recent person to receive the memorial for a government pension for <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4935.xml">Alfred Russel Wallace</ref> (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12953.xml">letter to P. L. Sclater, 29 December 1880</ref>). </note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">The article, headed ‘Professor Huxley on evolution’, was in <hi rend="italic">The Times</hi>, 25 December 1880, p. 4. Huxley’s lecture was delivered on 14 December 1880 at the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5302.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Zoological Society of London</ref> (<hi rend="italic">Nature</hi>, 23 December 1880, p. 187). </note>
        </div>   
       
